Q2. Role of Backend (BE)

The backend is the “behind the scenes” part of the application that runs on the server.

Server-side processing

Handles logic that cannot run securely on the client side

Processes user requests (login, payments, data fetch)

Executes business rules and calculations

Generates responses to send back to the frontend

Database handling

Connects to databases like MySQL, MongoDB, PostgreSQL etc.

Stores, updates, deletes, and retrieves application data

Ensures data consistency and reliability

Example: saving user details during signup

Security and authentication

Manages login and signup securely

Uses hashing, tokens, sessions, and encryption

Protects data from unauthorized access

Validates permissions (who can access what)
